# EAS Build uploads a tarball of the whole monorepo. .gitignore's `/target` only anchors to the
# repo root, so it misses Rust build artifacts under nested worktrees (agent worktrees, other
# feature checkouts living inside this tree) — those can be huge and their incremental-compile
# object files have tripped copy errors during tarball creation. None of it is needed for a
# mobile build.
.claude/worktrees/
.forge/worktrees/
**/target/
**/target-e2e/
